<html>	<head><meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html;charset=iso-8859-1"><title>www.parkermorse.net : running</title><link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles1.css"></head>	<body bgcolor="white" text="#999999"> <?require("common.php");conn();head();	$year = $HTTP_POST_VARS['year'];	$month = $HTTP_POST_VARS['month'];	$day = $HTTP_POST_VARS['day'];	$venue = $HTTP_POST_VARS['venue'];	$bq_time = $HTTP_POST_VARS['bq_time'];	$bq_stand = $HTTP_POST_VARS['bq_stand'];	$max_miles = $HTTP_POST_VARS['max_miles'];	$longrun_count = $HTTP_POST_VARS['longrun_count'];	$longest_run = $HTTP_POST_VARS['longest_run'];	$name = $HTTP_POST_VARS['name'];if ($HTTP_POST_VARS) {	$insert_query = "insert into boston_q values(null, '$year', '$month', '$day', '$venue', '$bq_time', '$bq_stand', '$max_miles', '$longrun_count', '$longest_run', '$name')";	$success = mysql_query($insert_query);	if ($success) {		echo "<p>Your qualifier has been added to the data. Thanks!</p>\r";	}}?><p class="sectionHead">training for a boston qualifier</p><p>This page was set up to answer an innocent question: what kind of mileage to peoplerun in order to qualify for the Boston Marathon? I've chosen to ask specifically for thehighest-mileage week in training for the qualifying performance. Also, out of curiosity, I'veasked for the length of the longest long run, and the number of long runs done in training,since those questions also came up in similar marathon discussions.</p><p>A "long run" is defined as a run of 30k (18.6 miles) or longer.</p><p>A "Boston Qualifier" is a marathon in which the participant runs a time which qualifiesthem for <a href="http://www.bostonmarathon.org/">the B.A.A. Boston Marathon</a>. This canbe run at Boston ("re-qualifying".) I've asked for the standard you needed to beat - pleaseuse the standard which applied for the qualifier you ran, not your current standard.</p><?$count_query = mysql_query("select count(*) from boston_q");$count_row = mysql_fetch_array($count_query);$entry_count = $count_row['count(*)'];echo "<p>There are $entry_count qualifying performances in the database.</p>\r";$week_query = mysql_query("select max(max_miles), min(max_miles), avg(max_miles) from boston_q");$week_row = mysql_fetch_array($week_query);$max_peak = $week_row['max(max_miles)'];$av_peak = $week_row['avg(max_miles)'];$min_peak = $week_row['min(max_miles)'];echo "<p>The average peak weekly mileage total is $av_peak. The peak weekly mileages range from $min_peak to $max_peak.</p>\r";$long_query = mysql_query("select max(longrun_count), min(longrun_count), avg(longrun_count) from boston_q");$long_row = mysql_fetch_array($long_query);$max_long = $long_row['max(longrun_count)'];$av_long = $long_row['avg(longrun_count)'];$min_long = $long_row['min(longrun_count)'];echo "<p>The average number of long runs (defined as runs equal or greater than 30k in distance) is $av_long. The number of long runs range from $min_long to $max_long.</p>\r";$length_query = mysql_query("select max(longest_run), min(longest_run), avg(longest_run) from boston_q");$length_row = mysql_fetch_array($length_query);$max_length = $length_row['max(longest_run)'];$av_length = $length_row['avg(longest_run)'];$min_length = $length_row['min(longest_run)'];echo "<p>The average distance of the longest run is $av_length. The longest-run distances range from $min_length to $max_length.</p>\r";?><p>Add your Boston-qualifying performance below:</p><form action="bq.php" method="post">  <div align="right">    <table border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3">      <tr>         <td align="right">Date (year, month, day)</td>        <td align="right">           <input type="text" name="year" size="5" maxlength="4">          &nbsp;          <select name="month">            <option selected>Select month</option>            <option>January</option>            <option>February</option>            <option>March</option>            <option>April</option>            <option>May</option>            <option>June</option>            <option>July</option>            <option>August</option>            <option>September</option>            <option>October</option>            <option>November</option>            <option>December</option>          </select>          &nbsp;          <input type="text" name="day" size="3" maxlength="2">        </td>      </tr>      <tr>         <td align="right">Race/Venue</td>        <td align="right">           <input type="text" name="venue" size="40" maxlength="40">        </td>      </tr>      <tr>         <td align="right">Qualifying time (use chip time, as the BAA does, if           it's different from your gun time)</td>        <td align="right">           <input type="text" name="bq_time" size="8" maxlength="7" value="h:mm:ss">        </td>      </tr>      <tr>         <td align="right">BQ Standard (what you had to run in order to qualify           at that time)</td>        <td align="right">           <input type="text" name="bq_stand" size="8" maxlength="7" value="h:mm:ss">        </td>      </tr>      <tr>         <td align="right">Total mileage in your highest-mileage week while training           for this qualifier (in miles)</td>        <td align="right">           <input type="text" name="max_miles" size="4" maxlength="3">        </td>      </tr>      <tr>         <td align="right">Number of &quot;long runs&quot; while training for this           qualifier (defined as runs of 30k or longer)</td>        <td align="right">           <input type="text" name="longrun_count" size="3" maxlength="2">        </td>      </tr>      <tr>         <td align="right">Distance of your longest long run while training for           this qualifier (in miles)</td>        <td align="right">           <input type="text" name="longest_run" size="4" maxlength="3">        </td>      </tr>      <tr>         <td align="right">Your name</td>        <td align="right">           <input type="text" name="name" size="40" maxlength="50">        </td>      </tr>      <tr>         <td>&nbsp;</td>        <td align="right">           <input type="submit" name="Submit" value="Submit">        </td>      </tr>    </table>  </div></form><p>The data follows:</p><table border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3"><tr>	<th>Name</th>	<th>Date</th>	<th>Venue</th>	<th>Time</th>	<th>Standard</th>	<th>Peak week</th>	<th># of long runs</th>	<th>Longest run</th></tr><?$data_query = mysql_query("select * from boston_q order by bq_stand, bq_time");$howmany = mysql_num_rows($data_query);for ($i = 0; $i < $howmany; $i++) {	echo "<tr>\r";	$data_row = mysql_fetch_array($data_query);	$year = $data_row['year'];	$month = $data_row['month'];	$day = $data_row['day'];	$venue = $data_row['venue'];	$bq_time = $data_row['bq_time'];	$bq_stand = $data_row['bq_stand'];	$max_miles = $data_row['max_miles'];	$longrun_count = $data_row['longrun_count'];	$longest_run = $data_row['longest_run'];	$name = $data_row['name'];	echo "<td>$name</td>\r";	echo "<td>$day $month $year</td>\r";	echo "<td>$venue</td>\r";	echo "<td>$bq_time</td>\r";	echo "<td>$bq_stand</td>\r";	echo "<td>$max_miles</td>\r";	echo "<td>$longrun_count</td>\r";	echo "<td>$longest_run</td>\r";	echo "</tr>\r";}echo "</table>\r";tail();?>	</body></html>